# CRTAIS — Implementation Plan (Phase 0 + Phase 1 Sprint 1)

This plan covers the initial build for the **Climate-Responsive Traditional Architecture Intelligence System** — an actionable platform that encodes vernacular architectural wisdom, performs thermal/airflow simulations, and generates practitioner-ready reports.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a very large, multi-month project. This plan covers **Phase 0 (preparation)** and **Phase 1 Sprint 1 (scaffold + site intake)**. Subsequent phases will be planned after this foundation is built, tested, and reviewed.

---

## User Review Required

1. **Next.js version** — The plan uses **Next.js 14** with the App Router. Confirm this is acceptable.
2. **Tailwind CSS version** — Will use **Tailwind CSS v3** (the user spec says Tailwind, overriding the default vanilla CSS guideline). Confirm.
3. **Map provider** — Plan uses **Leaflet** (free, no API key) instead of Mapbox. Switch to Mapbox if preferred (requires API key).
4. **Database hosting** — Initial dev uses local Docker containers for PostgreSQL/PostGIS and MongoDB. Confirm Docker is available, or specify alternative.
5. **Pilot site locations** — The plan seeds 3 example sites (Jaipur, Kutch, Coorg). Please confirm or provide your preferred pilot sites and climate zones.

